# Project Context
Project Name: "AI 萌宠造物 (PetMagic)"
Description: An AI-powered wallpaper and sticker generator for pets using AI models.
Goal: Build a high-quality, portfolio-ready application.

# Tech Stack
- Backend: FastAPI, Pydantic, Celery, Redis.
- Frontend: Uni-app (Vue 3), TypeScript, Pinia.
- Deployment: Docker.

# Coding Guidelines (Strictly Follow)
1. Frontend (Uni-app):
   - Use Vue 3 Composition API `<script setup lang="ts">`.
   - Use standard SCSS for styling. DO NOT use Tailwind CSS (to avoid compatibility issues with WeChat).
   - Ensure specific WeChat Mini Program tags are used (e.g., `<view>`, `<image>`) instead of HTML tags (`<div>`, `<img>`).

2. Backend (FastAPI):
   - Strictly use Pydantic for data validation (Request/Response schemas).
   - Use `async/await` for all I/O operations.
   - Follow PEP 8 style guidelines.

3. General:
   - Always prioritize code readability and maintainability.
   - Add comments for complex logic.

